Executes outside the wiki repo (capture infra, likely joelclaw/pi-tools) â€” coordinate with whatever session-capture sessions are active on this machine before touching shared pipelines. Resolved when a real day's ledger exists on disk and a re-run of the feasibility check flips its verdict for at least one runtime.

## Resolution (2026-07-12)

Built by pi worker (wJ:p5, callsign Harried Windle), verified end-to-end and activated by the steering session. Code: `pi-tools/change-ledger/` (commit `9f2ce1a`); schema note `pi-tools/.brain/resources/pi-session-change-ledger.svx`.

- **Pi runtime v1, additive**: successful `write`/`edit` tool results append hash-proven JSONL records â€” sessionId, machineId, repo remote + worktree + HEAD, canonical path, pre/post git blob hashes, immutable per-turn `changeSetId` â€” to `~/.local/state/joelclaw/change-ledger/YYYY-MM-DD.jsonl`. Bash mutations emit an honest `bash-mutation-unattributed` marker (no command parsing, per the memo).
- **Deterministic attribution proven live** by the steering session on a scratch repo: a real pi session wrote a file; `attribute-commit.ts` matched the commit by blob-hash equality (`4215fa43â€¦`), propagated the changeSetId and sessionId, zero unattributed paths, no timestamps involved. The feasibility memo's contract holds for Pi.
- **Activated on flagg**: symlinked into `~/.pi/agent/extensions/change-ledger`; smoke-tested (clean session startup; read-only sessions correctly write nothing). Every pi mutation on this machine ledgers from now on â€” the real day's ledger accrues from today.
- Remaining, deliberately out of this ticket: Claude/Codex runtime capture, bash worktree diffing, supersession markers, git-rewrite lineage, blaine activation (pi-tools sync + symlink there). Graph schema v3 `session-change` edges can now be built the moment a few days of real ledger exist.
